thread.title: Mooy assists as Huddersfield go nine games unbeaten
thread.title_full: Mooy assists as Huddersfield go nine games unbeaten

title: Mooy assists as Huddersfield go nine games unbeaten
text:
Mooy assists as Huddersfield go nine games unbeaten Aaron Mooy in action against Barnsley (Getty Images) Australia's Aaron Mooy has assisted in Huddersfield Town's 1-1 draw away to Barnsley in the Championship, as the Terriers made it nine matches unbeaten. By Tweet 
Mooy picked up his seventh assist of the season when he drilled in a perfect corner kick that defender Michael Hefele was able to head straight past Barnsley's keeper. 
Huddersfield dominated the match but were unable to convert their numerous chances due to some great last ditch defending by Barnsley. 
Mooy was once again the most involved player in the game, having more touches (88) and completing more passes (60) than anyone on the pitch. Good half from Town. Aaron Mooy is playing a different game to everyone else on the pitch. The Hef getting better every game! #htafc 
— Richard Kosmala (@superkos) February 25, 2017 
The former Melbourne City midfielder's performance wasn't all positive though, he managed to pick up a yellow card in the first half for a heavy challenge on Josh Scowen. Best player in the Championship? 
— George Elek (@georgeelek) February 25, 2017 
Huddersfield, who have only lost one of their past 17 matches, remain in third spot on the Championship table, four points and a game in hand clear of Leeds United while five points short of second placed Newcastle United. 
Fellow Aussies Callum Elder and Ryan Williams both started on the bench for Barnsley, with Williams coming off the bench in the 93rd minute as the Tykes held on for a point. 
Elsewhere, Massimo Luongo was an unused substitute in Queens Park Rangers' 2-1 loss to Preston North End. As was Brad Smith in Bournemouth's 2-1 loss to West Brom. 
Mile Jedinak played the full 90 minutes in Aston Villa's 1-0 win over Derby, creating one chance and making four interceptions. Jedinak is an absoloute monster in midfield! him & Lansbury were outstanding today! #avfc 
— Aston Villa Updates (@AstonVilla_info) February 25, 2017 
Bailey Wright also played a full match as his Bristol City recorded a surprise 2-2 draw with high-flying Newcastle at St. james' Park. Bristol are currently just one place above relegation. 
In the Dutch top tier Jason Davidson had a roller-coaster match, setting up Groningen's second goal to give them a 2-0 lead only to see it evaporate in the second-half and lose 3-2 as well as pick up a yellow card in the process.
